    • Constructor Detail

      • FastaIndexRecord

        public FastaIndexRecord(long seqLength,
                        long firstBaseOffset,
                        int basesPerLine,
                        int bytesPerLineIncludingEol)
        Constructor that takes the fields of a record in the order that they are listed in an fai file.
        Parameters:
        seqLength - the length of a sequence in bases.
        firstBaseOffset - the offset (in bytes) to the first base of the sequence. This is not to be confused with the first byte offset of the defline.
        basesPerLine - the number of bases per line on a full line (the final line may be shorter).
        bytesPerLineIncludingEol - the number of bytes per line including any line terminators.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if any fields are negative, or firstBaseOffset is determined to be before the end of a defline or if bytesPerLineIncludingEol < basesPerLine
